org.araneaframework.http
Interface PopupWindowContext

All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
StandardPopupFilterWidget
public interface PopupWindowContext
extends Serializable

An interface for manipulating popup windows (each popup window corresponding to server-side "thread"). It is mainly used for opening new windows client-side. To make it work, one must also register popups client side using the <ui:registerPopups/> tag.

Author:
Taimo Peelo
See Also:
PopupRegistrationHtmlTag

open

public String open(Message startMessage,
                   PopupWindowProperties properties,
                   Widget opener)
Registers a new thread-level service server-side and gives started service means of communicating with its opener and vice-versa.

Parameters:
startMessage - The message sent to the newly created service (thread).
properties - The properties specifying behaviour and appearance of the creatable popup window.
opener - The widget that is registered as an opener of the created thread.
Returns:
The thread level ID of the created and registered service.

Parameters:

properties - The properties specifying behaviour and appearance of creatable popup window.
opener - The widget that is registered as an opener of the created thread.

getOpener

public Widget getOpener()
Returns the widget that opened the calling thread-level service (popup).

Returns:
The opener of the thread-level service, null when calling service does not have registered opener.

getPopups

public Map getPopups()
Provides all opened and unclosed popups.

Returns:
A Map of popups where the keys are IDs of the threads (Strings) and the value are instances of PopupServiceInfo.
